<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Alielgo</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-02 01:26:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Let me clear up some information on this. <BR>
<BR>
First, Sir Lucan WAS a Paladin.  He was stripped of his powers, and as such, he is a level 48 Warrior model with approximately 8000 hps.  He DOES spawn into an undead form, and THIS drops the testimony.  The undead form is NOTHING compared to Sir Lucan himself.  <BR>
<BR>
Second, his friends are a Guard Jaczen (sp?) and Brother Jentry.  They do NOT LH on him, but they might as well, because Brother Jentry is a Cleric and will complete and greater heal Lucan all day long.  He must be separated from Lucan at all costs, or you will not drop Lucan.<BR>
<BR>
Third, no WAY do you need two full groups of level 50's to kill Lucan.  I know, because our guild (Sentinals) killed him tonight on the Povar server with NOBODY over level 41.<BR>
This is what we had on the raid:<BR>
<BR>
Level 41 Paladin<BR>
Level 41 Monk<BR>
Level 40 Cleric<BR>
Level 39 Cleric<BR>
Level 38 Paladin<BR>
Level 37 Druid<BR>
Level 36 Ranger<BR>
Level 34 Druid<BR>
Level 32 Rogue<BR>
<BR>
The 34th lvl Druid did NOT fight, as he strictly kited Jentry around W Freeport.  Tanks will take a BEATING, and you WILL die.  However if you pull him close enough to the zone, you can die, respawn in the zone, and you can grab your weapon and start slugging again.  He double attacks for 119, and dual wields.  He CAN be disarmed, as our Monk took out one of his weapons.  <BR>
<BR>
Would have dropped a lot sooner if we hadn't have had to just slug it out and melee him to death.  Bring two high level wizards, and a balanced party and he will drop.  <BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
