<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nien</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-09 15:36:21</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The faction needed with Brother Hayle is kindly (one step above amiable).  However, for me, Brother Hayle is one faction step below the Temple of Thunder (paladin guild in qeynos).  So I had to get warmly with them, and in turn was kindly with Brother Hayle.<BR>
<BR>
To raise faction with them, there are several quests you can do, but the most effective one is Bandit Sashes.  Kill bandit's in West Karana and every now and then they drop a NO DROP red Bandit Sash.  There's a few camps around, but the easiest is bandit hill, near the ogre camp...there's about 8 or 10 bandits there on a pretty quick spawn.  After you kill them, there's a couple bandits that spawn at the base of the hill and about 3 or 4 more over at that farmhouse nearby.  I filled my inven with sashes (about 15 free slots) and it raised me a faction level.  Oh yeah, you turn those sashes in one at a time to Chesgard somebody in the Temple of Thunder in South Qeynos.  He also give you back a bronze weapon which you can sell to the guy next to him for a couple plat a piece.<BR>
<BR>
You can also turn in bone chips (2 at a time) to Lashun Novashine, a newb looking human that's usually in the newbie area near the gate walking around shouting some annoying stuff.  Either there or on the ramp to the space ship at the Temple of Life.<BR>
<BR>
These two are how I went from indif to warmly with these qeynos punks  :)  Very annoying, but worth it in the end I suppose.<BR>
<BR>
I too am very interested in knowing whether or not SoulFire can be recharged in the Temple of Marr in Freeport as being reported by various sites, however, nobody has mentioned a specific NPC that does it.  And I don't exactly want to go around handing my SF in to random NPC's to test it out either  :P</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nien</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-09 15:56:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oh, I forgot to mention:  The actual faction you're wanting to raise is "KnightsofThunder"<BR>
<BR>
And before you can hand in your items, Brother Hayle must respond positively to "What proof of nobility?"  Basically, you have to be kindly with him, or else he will say something like "I may only talk about things like this with our most trusted members", but if you have high enough faction he'll give you the list of things he needs (note, testimony of truth, hilt, and BSOF)</font></td></tr></table>
